            <label key="61a27cd6b459c369ed382e343ab0c944">
                <text>Carbon Footprint of Food</text>
            </label>
            <label key="0286a8556e84fd39aea75f2eff8378a3">
                <text>A carbon footprint is defined as the total amount of all greenhouse gas emissions that are released across all stages of a product’s life-cycle, including land use, production, transportation and waste disposal.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="386daa6410a16221506fac6403dc4318">
                <text>The food industry is responsible for about 22% of total human-made greenhouse gas emissions. Different foods have different carbon footprints. The graph shows the greenhouse gas emissions for different stages of the life-cycle of some foods.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f5ef75ca0cdce007a69b08dbffef588c">
                <text>
                    <strong>Food: greenhouse gas emissions across the life-cycle</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
